# Testing, CI/CD, and Deployment

## Testing

### Playwright
- Configuration: [playwright.config.js](mdc:playwright.config.js) — local runs use a dedicated dev port (`E2E_PORT`, default **3100**) so the Playwright `webServer` does not collide with a normal `next dev` on port 3000.
- Tests: [tests/e2e/](mdc:tests/e2e/) — homepage, blog, contact, newsletter, links, speaking, zag-matrix
- Page objects: [tests/e2e/pageObjects/](mdc:tests/e2e/pageObjects/)
- Default: run E2E against **local** dev (`npm run dev` + `npm run test:e2e`); use production `BASE_URL` only when intentionally testing live site
- **Pre-deploy:** Prefer `npm run test:e2e` and `npm run build` before merging to `main`

### Standards
- Cover critical user flows: navigation, forms, blog load, newsletter paths
- Keep selectors maintainable (prefer stable names over brittle counts)

## Continuous Integration

- [`.github/workflows/playwright.yml`](mdc:.github/workflows/playwright.yml) — E2E on push/PR to `main`
- [`.github/workflows/deploy.yml`](mdc:.github/workflows/deploy.yml) — production deploy workflow
- Quality gates: TypeScript build; tests green; Next.js build succeeds

## Deployment Strategy

- **Platform:** Vercel hosting; **production URL:** https://sheridanrichey.com
- **Primary method:** Git-based (GitOps). `website/vercel.json` may disable native Git auto-deploy — follow [AGENTS.md](mdc:AGENTS.md) and the deploy workflow for the actual path to production
- **Trigger:** Push to `main` (and/or GitHub Actions workflow as configured)
- **Preview:** PR preview deployments on Vercel when enabled
- **Fallback:** Vercel CLI manual deploy if needed

### Helper script
- [website/deploy.ps1](mdc:website/deploy.ps1) — PowerShell helper for commit/deploy steps

### Git workflow
1. Develop locally
2. Commit with clear messages (conventional format preferred)
3. Push feature branch and open PR to `main` (do not push implementation directly to `main`)
4. Wait for required CI checks to pass (Playwright + build/type checks as configured)
5. Merge PR to `main`
6. Verify GitHub Actions and Vercel production deployment, then run focused smoke checks for changed flows

## Vercel configuration

- **Config files:** [vercel.json](mdc:vercel.json) (root), [website/vercel.json](mdc:website/vercel.json) (app)
- **Root directory:** Vercel project should use `website/` as the app root when applicable
- **IDs and team settings:** stored in Vercel dashboard — do not commit secrets; project/team IDs belong in Vercel UI, not in repo docs as authoritative config

## Environment variables

- **Secrets:** Beehiiv, Resend, etc. — set in Vercel for production; use `website/.env.local` locally (see `website/.env.example`)
- Never commit API keys or tokens

## Rollback & monitoring

- **Rollback:** revert commit or redeploy previous Vercel deployment
- Monitor deployment status, Core Web Vitals, and errors via Vercel (and Analytics if enabled)
